          <h4>Social Responsibility</h4>
          	<p>PiSA demonstrates its commitment to the community through the Stella Vega Foundation named after the late wife of PiSA’s owner. Through the Stella Vega foundation the community has been supported during the 1st half of 2013 in the following programs:</p>
              <p>Health: 2,645 hemodialysis sessions, 1,339 medicines delivered, 68 patients benefited from clinical studies.</p>
              <p>Disasters: Support in natural disasters as in the case of Hurricanes Ingrid and Manuel and support throughout the ecocide occurred in the Dam of Valencia in Jalisco.</p>
              <p>Food: 10,832 Pantries delivered to different institutions and 500 Pantries delivered to low- income families.</p>
              <p>Donations: More than 66 different institutions have received donations from PiSA and 19,332 dialysis bags given to patients with kidney problems.</p>
              <p>Social Responsibility:
